{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-05217/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-05217"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:52:17"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A reporter asks questions."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05217/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-05217","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05217/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-05217"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05217/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05217/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05217/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05217/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05217/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05217/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05217/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05217/canvas/1/71ffe9d0-42d6-4f00-8863-656cce6cb4ed","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T20:15:58.984Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>World War II looms in the background of <em>Phantom Thread</em>. Although never a subject of extended discussion by any of the characters, the postwar context means that the events of the war continue to play a role in their lives. Alma, for example, may have been a refugee. Reynolds refers to how he liberated some fabric from Flanders. Here, the reporter attempts to interrogate Rubio about rumors that he sold visas to Jews during the world, thus profiting from their plight. In an interview with <em>The Hollywood Reporter</em>, Vicky Krieps speaks about drawing on her grandmother’s wartime experience (The Hollywood Reporter, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW114523336 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m_95U_RQUTg\"><u>In Studio With 'Phantom Thread's' Vicky Krieps</u></a>”).</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05217/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:32.46076850546153,28.339292218259047,334.8412112259971,266.2181499261448"}}}]}]}]}